Acoustic measurements throughout the ~15-35cms range tend to plot significantly to the left of a rating developed with historical measurements. Acoustic measurements have been known to suffer from QA/QC concerns such as: •	Low intensity/backscatter issues, •	Remote boat limitations (edges, control, check measurements).  Note that acoustic measurement analysis suggest that the default Power/Power extrapolation is not the best fit. Measurements post ~2016 have had this extrapolation revised and may be contributing to the large negative rating errors.  The decision has been made (2023-10-24) to discard the outlier acoustic measurements and rely on the statistical strength of the rating. Efforts will be made to have the cableway repaired and/or relocated to a location where conventional/acoustic analysis may be attempted and transect characteristics are good for a larger range of stage.   Sources:Manual Measurement suspect! GGA was chosen for QRev but results in a unacceptable directional bias of +/-35%. It has been noted in the past that ADCP measurements in the 15-30m3/s are suspect due to low backscatter/SNR and shallow shores. Due to the channel configuration, i.e. wide and shallow with most of the flow concentrated in a narrow deep middle section, I believe QRev may bias the extrapolation method and exponent. comparison with conventional measurements in this range is also poor. For these reasons, I have choosen not to shift to this measurement in 2019.-WH, Feb 21, 2023.

All transects looked OK, there was only a 1% standard deviation in Area & Width among the 16 transects but there was an 8%SD in Average Velocity. Assuming the instrument was measuring accurately the river was not in steady flow caused by strong winds.   Do not use this mmnt in curve development. Sources:Import,Manual
